<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN213-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – vañci; tuṟai – tuṇaivañci. avaṉ makkaṇmēṟ ceṉṟāṉaip pullāṟṟūr eyiṟṟiyaṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
  </div>
    <div xml:id="PN213">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>maṇṭama raṭṭa mataṉuṭai nōṉṟāḷ</l>
<l>veṇkuṭai viḷakkum viṟaṟkeḻu vēntē</l>
<l>poṅkunī ruṭuttavim malartalai yulakattu</l>
<l>niṉṟalai vanta viruvarai niṉaippiṟ</l>
<l>ṟoṉṟuṟai tuppiṉiṉ pakaiñaru malla</l>
<l>ramarveṅ kāṭciyoṭu māṟetir peḻuntavar</l>
<l>niṉaiyuṅ kālai nīyu maṟṟavark</l>
<l>kaṉaiyai yallai yaṭumāṉ ṟōṉṟal</l>
<l>parantupaṭu nallicai yeyti maṟṟunī</l>
<l>yuyarntō rulaka meytip piṉṉu</l>
<l>moḻitta tāya mavarkkurit taṉṟē</l>
<l>yataṉāl, aṉṉa tātalu maṟivōy naṉṟu</l>
<l>miṉṉuṅ kēṇmati yicaivey yōyē</l>
<l>niṉṟa tuppoṭu niṉkuṟit teḻunta</l>
<l>veṇṇil kāṭci yiḷaiyōr tōṟpi</l>
<l>ṉiṉperuñ celvam yārkkeñ cuvaiyē</l>
<l>yamarveñ celva nīyavark kulaiyi</l>
<l>ṉikaḻuna ruvappap paḻiyeñ cuvaiyē</l>
<l>yataṉā, loḻikati lattainiṉ maṟaṉē valvirain</l>
<l>teḻumati vāḻkaniṉ ṉuḷḷa maḻintōrk</l>
<l>kēma mākuniṉ ṟāṇiḻaṉ mayaṅkātu</l>
<l>ceytal vēṇṭumā ṉaṉṟē vāṉō</l>
<l>rarumpeṟa lulakat tāṉṟavar</l>
<l>vitumpuṟu viruppoṭu viruntetir koḷaṟkē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="2">O victorious king whose white parasol shines brightly, </l>
<l corresp="1">with a powerful sturdy foot, who killed in rushing fight, </l>
<l corresp="4">if you think of the two [men] who have come to your place </l>
<l corresp="3">in this world, a blooming area yoked with foaming water, </l>
<l corresp="5">they are not enemies of you with a vigour than stays of old, </l>
<l corresp="6">those who have risen in opposition with a view keen on a fight, </l>
<l>and you, at the time you think about [it], are not</l>
<l>like those others, o appearance on a murderous animal. (7f.)</l>
<l corresp="9">You, having attained widespread fame, </l>
<l corresp="10">after you have attained the world of the upper ones, moreover </l>
<l corresp="11">the heritage you have finished with will be rightfully their’s. </l>
<l corresp="12">Therefore, you who know well that it will be thus, </l>
<l corresp="13">from now on listen, you keen on fame: </l>
<l corresp="15">If the young men, [whose army is a] sight without count, are defeated </l>
<l corresp="14">who have risen aiming at you with [still] lasting vigour, </l>
<l corresp="16">to whom will you leave your great wealth? </l>
<l corresp="17">O lord keen on a fight, if you are ruined by them, </l>
<l corresp="18">you will leave behind blame while those who despise you rejoice. </l>
<l corresp="19">Therefore, let your bravery be curbed. In great haste </l>
<l corresp="20a-c">rise – let your heart live [long]. </l>
<l corresp="20d-21">Without that the shade of your foot would be obscured that is protection to those in ruin, </l>
<l corresp="22a-c">you must act well </l>
<l corresp="24">in order to be received as a guest with tremorous/eager longing </l>
<l corresp="23">by those who ended up in the world difficult to obtain, </l>
<l corresp="22d">	by the celestials. </l>
</lg>
